    <note>Zhou(1) Wuzhong [7199] Zhuangzhong's [484] elder brother, Yang(2) Xun's [7398] son-in-law, Han(1) Yuanzhou's [7232] father-in-law. His great grandfather, Heng [24372], and unnamed grandfather, K [24373], did not hold office. Yang(2) Shi does not name father, L [24374], but he held office and was once prefect of Guangde county. It is unlikely that he would have reached such a postition w/o some member of the lineage having earned a jinshi degree. I am assuming that this was Zhou(1) Chang [16400], a Pucheng jinshi in 1073, who is, therefore, identified as uncle of Wuzhong and Zhuangzhong [484]. In any case, Chang must be a lineage member. Yang Shi, WJ, 36.1a-12a. CBD, 2, 1480.</note>
